<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Brothers Come Out 1-2 at Madrid Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Brothers Alberto and Alexis Cuba
brought home the gold and silver titles after shaking off the pack
to dominate the Madrid marathon on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Alberto led nearly a minute ahead of Alexis and clocked a
winning time of two hours 16 minutes -- the best time for five
years in the event.
</P>
<P>
The women's race was won by their Cuban compatriot Sergia
Martinez.
</P>
<P>
Alberto, the 1991 Pan-American champion, won the family battle
when he pulled away on the hilly section in the approach to the
finish in Madrid's Retiro park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
