<HEADLINE> 11 Injured in Explosion in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were injured
when an explosive device went off Saturday evening at a bar in
Dire Dawa, the second largest city of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency today quoted Abahoy Kasa, police
chief of the city, as saying that the injured, including six
workers of the bar, were sent home after treatment at the Dil
Chora Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The bar is located near the railway station in Dire Dawa and
is frequented by travelers.
</P>
<P>
Police are on the trail of the culprits and have asked for
cooperation from the public.
</P>
<P>
Three explosions occurred in capital Addis Ababa, killing one
and injuring 75 others between April 12 and 14, this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
