<HEADLINE> Labor Issue to Be Probe in Africa's Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The governments of African
countries have been urged to ensure that the export processing
zones they are implementing do not result in the exploitation of
the workers by multi-national companies.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by more than 90 delegates who attended the
five-day conference for Southern African Development Community
(SADC) member states on food security which ended in Darwendale
near Harare at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
These zones, delegates resolved, should be monitored to guard
against their promoting international economies at the expense of
labor.
</P>
<P>
Quoting experiences from other countries, experts said some
export processing zones had attracted cheap, docile labor for
multi-national companies which exploited and impoverished their
lives.
</P>
<P>
A comprehensive report documenting resolutions on land
reforms, food security and labor issues would be produced for
possible implementation by the respective governments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German President Asks for Forgiveness for Guernica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- German President Roman Herzog today
asked residents of Guernica for forgiveness 60 years after the
northern Spanish town was bombed down by German warplanes during
the Spanish Civil War, a news release issued by German presidency
said.
</P>
<P>
"I want to face up to the past and explicitly acknowledge the
guilty part played by German aviators," said Herzog in a statement
read out by German Ambassador to Spain, Henning Wegener, to a
ceremony in Guernica marking the 60th anniversary of the attack.
</P>
<P>
This represents Germany's first official admission of
responsibility for the bombing.
</P>
<P>
"I address my message of commemoration, sympathy and grief to
you, the survivors of the attack and witnesses of the horror
endured, " Herzog said.
</P>
<P>
On April 26, 1937, during the Spanish Civil War, German Nazis
sent bombers of the "Legion Condor" squadron to attack Guernica in
assistance of the troops of Francisco Franco against those of the
Repubicans. The war ended in 1939 with Franco becoming dictator of
Spain.
</P>
<P>
The attack reduced around three-quarters of the defenceless
Basque town to rubble. The death toll was never established, with
estimates ranging from 300 to 1,500.
</P>
<P>
The Guernica attack also represents the first massive air
bombardment of a town or city in the history of Europe. Historians
believe that the raid was used by German Nazis to test air strike
tactics deployed later during World War II. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Upgrades Prison Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Prison Service is
upgrading its services and expanding the jail space to
accommodate 4,600 more prisoners as the existing jails can no
longer cope with the soaring crime-rate.
</P>
<P>
Officials said work had already started on four sites for the
new prisons.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that when these institutions are completed they will
go a long way to alleviate our overcrowding problem," said an
official.
</P>
<P>
Although the jails have an ideal capacity of 16,000 prisoners,
Zimbabwe's current prison population is 18,000.
</P>
<P>
Last year there was a presidential amnesty which saw 4,000
prisoners being released to create space in the prisons after the
population soared to 22,000 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
However, This proved a temporary solution as most of the
pardoned criminals soon returned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
