<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents in Greece Kill 27, Injure 261 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five people have been
killed and 261 injured in 190 road accidents in Greece since April
23 during thousands of Athenians abandoned the capital to spend
the orthodox Easter holiday in the provinces or on islands.
</P>
<P>
Greek police said that Most accidents occurred on the secondary
road network rather than on the main national highways.
</P>
<P>
They regarded the exodus as one of the biggest in recent years,
saying that buses, trains and ships booked to capacity.
</P>
<P>
Demand for train, ferry and air tickets rose by more than 50
percent as compared to last year, they said. 
</P>
