<HEADLINE> East African Cooperation Urged to Admit Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Former Tanzanian President
Mwalimu Julius Nyerere today asked Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania,
the three member states of the East African Cooperation (EAC),
to grant EAC membership to Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
At the official opening of the German-East Africa Dialogue in
Arusha, a northern Tanzanian town where EAC was formed in March
last year, Nyerere said EAC should warmly welcome landlocked
Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
"I understand that Rwanda has already applied to joint the
East African Cooperation. That country should be welcomed into
the East African family without hesitation," he was quoted by
reports reaching here as saying.
</P>
<P>
"It would be good for Rwanda, good for East Africa and good
for Africa generally," he said. An EAC summit is scheduled to be
held there next Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere said he was certain that as soon as Burundi has a
legal government on behalf of its people, Burundi would also
apply to join the regional grouping.
</P>
<P>
"When that happens - and I hope and pray it will happen soon -
that country should be welcomed with open arms," he told the
participants in the three-day dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called on the three EAC member nations to be
committed to regional cooperation on the basis of equity which
can be achieved through the organization's choice of projects.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the region's attempts to build greater
cooperation among African countries, there was a need to have
courage and vision to overcome the difficulties causing by
languages and borders imposed by colonialists.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation is essential for the people and the
governments in the EAC region, he said, adding that it does not
replace the need for national efforts to improve the internal
infrastructures and increase investments.
</P>
<P>
The three-day dialogue has been organized by the Friendrich
Ebert Stifiung in collaboration with the German Science and
Research Foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
