<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Alain Juppe
said this evening that he is not "absolutely" the candidate for
the prime minister's seat, after the legislative elections are
held on May 25 and June 1.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with French Television One, Juppe said that the
nomination of prime minister after the legislative elections is
the "prerogative of the President of the Republic."
</P>
