<HEADLINE> Mubarak: No Cabinet Reshuffle in the Offing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
today turned down the speculation that a major cabinet reshuffle
is near.
</P>
<P>
No cabinet reshuffle will take place in the near future,
Mubarak told reporters who accompanied him on his flight home from
Jeddah, Saudi Arabia today.
</P>
<P>
Several issues should be first completed, for instance, the
state budget, before thinking of a cabinet reshuffle, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The reshuffle, however, will be announced at the appropriate
time," he said, returning home following a two-day Gulf tour which
took him to Kuwait and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Egyptian parliament has expressed confidence in
and support for the government of Prime Minister Kamal
el-Ganzouri, amid wild speculation that a major cabinet shake-up
is near.
</P>
<P>
However, Egyptian journalists and political pundits put on
their guessing caps in the past few weeks and spun rumors about a
major shake-up of many of the country's most entrenched ministers.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri's team replaced the government led by former prime
minister Atef Sidki in January 1996 in the last cabinet shake-up.
</P>
