<HEADLINE> Jordan, Algeria Sign Cultural Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Jordan and Algeria signed a
bilateral agreement on cultural and scientific cooperation here
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Jordanian news agency Petra, the agreement
particularly encourages direct exchanges and cooperation between
Jordanian and Algerian universities and institutes.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will accordingly boost their cooperation in
the field of scientific research, including the exchange of
scientific data and technology, training of scholars and experts
in various scientific domains.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also covers the exchange of textbooks,
scientific, literary and art publications and bulletins.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides for further cooperation in fields of
Arabization of university education, reciprocal recognition of
certificates, scientific degrees and systems of future predictions.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, to be effective for the next two years, was
signed by Jordanian Minister of Education and Higher Education
Munther Masri and the visiting Algerian Minister of Higher
Education and Scientific Research Abu Bakr Buzeid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
