<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor on Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Top priority will be given to the
building of basic farmland and rural infrastructure in the work of
poverty relief, and primary leaders at all levels are the keys to
the work, State Councillor Chen Junsheng has said.
</P>
<P>
He called on local officials to do the job in a down-to-earth
manner, during an inspection tour of Luliang Prefecture in north
China's Shanxi Province April 24-28.
</P>
<P>
"There is no short cut for poverty relief, and no big talk, no
cheating or trickery are allowed in this respect," he warned.
</P>
<P>
His investigation and research were focused on the combination
of poverty alleviation and grass-roots Party building, development
of basic farmland, auction of wasteland, and women's role in the
anti-poverty campaign.
</P>
<P>
Experience gained in the prefecture showed that there are many
ways wherewith to overcome poverty, but the must is to have a
staunch village Party branch, he said, adding that poverty relief
divorced from Party building will be inadequate.
</P>
<P>
Building infrastructure and improving farmers' skills are the
most important guidelines to better improve the conditions in the
poor areas, he noted, as economic growth in poor areas relies
heavily on science, technology and education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
