<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenyang Becomes First Inland Port of Entry in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- This capital of Northeast
China's Liaoning Province became the first inland port of
entry in the northeastern part of China as of today.
</P>
<P>
The first express train shuttling between Shenyang and Dalian
moved out of the city's East Railway Station today, with
standard containers on board, and started its first trip along the
length of the Shenyang-Dalian Railway.
</P>
<P>
This made Shenyang the first inland port of entry of the
Shenyang Railway Bureau, which is the operator of the railway
networks in northeast China. Containers from neighboring regions
can be transported to any part of the world via Dalian Port on the
southernmost tip of the province.
</P>
<P>
The railway station now boasts an annual handling capacity of
55,000 containers. There are railway connections from the station
to many other inland cities and border cities in the northeastern
part of China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
