<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Singaporean Prime Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng met here today
with his Singaporean counterpart Goh Chok Tong, who is currently
on a working visit to China.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, in the Great Hall of the People, the two
leaders exchanged views on issues of common concern. Reviewing the
growth of bilateral relations, they expressed the desire to
further strengthen cooperation so as to create a still closer
cooperative ties of good neighborliness based on mutual trust and
to carry it forward into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"We are satisfied to see that as we enter the seventh year
since China and Singapore established their diplomatic relations,
the two countries have achieved remarkable results in all fields
of mutually beneficial friendly cooperation," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that the two countries enjoy a very good relationship
and there are no problems between them. Singapore is optimistic
about the prospects for bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral economic and trade ties, Li said that economic and
trade cooperation between the two countries has been growing
steadily, with the volume of two-way trade topping that between
China and any other ASEAN country.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological cooperation between the two sides
is also expanding, he said. He added that the Chinese government
is ready to work with the Singaporean side to continuously advance
the development of bilateral economic and trade cooperation on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Goh on China's domestic situation. He recalled that
in the past two decades China has achieved great progress and
success by firmly carrying out the policy of reform and opening-up
that the late Comrade Deng Xiaoping formulated. He said that China
enjoys political stability because the leadership with Jiang Zemin
at the core has won the support and trust of the people. China
will continue to march forward along the road of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics that Deng Xiaoping
initiated.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that the Chinese leadership is strong and capable of
dealing with all kinds of challenges.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the Singaporean guests about the Chinese
central government's policy on Hong Kong after its return to the
motherland. He pointed out that the situation of Hong Kong is
generally good. The general conditions for the smooth transfer
have already been achieved, he said. More and more people are
attaining confidence in the smooth handover of power and long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Goh invited Premier Li to visit Singapore later this year. Li
accepted the invitation and thanked Goh for it.
</P>
<P>
After the talks Li and Goh attended the signing ceremony for
two documents, namely the Treaty on Judicial Assistance in Civil
and Commercial Matters between the People's Republic of China and
the Republic of Singapore, and the Terminal Service Agreement
between the China Ocean Shipping Group Company and Port
of Singapore Authority.
</P>
<P>
Li hosted a welcome banquet for Goh and his party this
evening.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
