<HEADLINE> Australia to Grant Nepal 7.7 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Australian government has
agreed to provide a grant assistance of over 7.7 million US
dollars to Nepal for the continuous implementation of a forestry
project, the Nepali Finance Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant was signed here today between the two
governments, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The amount will be used for the new phase of an on-going
community forestry project in two central Nepali districts, which
started in 1992 and is expected to end in 2002, it said.
</P>
<P>
The forestry project aims to encourage local people's
participation in the development and management of forests.
</P>
<P>
Earlier phases of the project have made considerable
improvements in resources use, conservation and household income
as well as local infrastructure like drinking water, the ministry
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
