<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IOM Chief Visits Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the International
Organization for Migration (IOM) James Puncell today arrived here
to start his four-day visit to Angola.
</P>
<P>
The aim of his visit was to mobilize fund to continue the
implementation of the resettlement project of disbanded soldiers
from the former warring sides in Angola.
</P>
<P>
Puncell told reporters that it is necessary to make
international donors realize that money is critical for carrying
out the resettlement project which needs 28 million US Dollars.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that his organization will take some
measures to ensure the disbanded soldiers be more properly
resettled in Angola.
</P>
<P>
Among the measures, the IOM will set up 2,000 mini-enterprises
to receive the abundant soldiers and also provide vocational
training for them.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Angola, he will meet Angolan leaders and
representatives from international donors to mobilize more
money for the resettlement project in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
