<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Exhibition Shows Famous Bridges Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition featuring models
of multi-functional bridges opened here today to mark the opening
of the Tsing Ma Bridge, the world's longest rail and road traffic
suspension bridge.
</P>
<P>
The Tsing Ma Bridge, spanning 1,377 meters across the sea,
signifies the success of one of the most spectacular schemes in
the Hong Kong Airport Core Program. A grand ceremony was held
Sunday in celebration of the opening of the Lantau Link, to which
the Tsing Ma Bridge is a part.
</P>
<P>
Organizing the Living Bridges Exhibition aims to demonstrate
man's endeavors behind bridges in overcoming natural obstacles,
according to Ronald Leung Ding-bong, chairman of the Urban
Council, the co-organizer.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the model of the Tsing Ma Bridge, the show features
15 architectural models of renowned bridges worldwide, such as Old
London Bridge, the Ponte Vecchio and the Pont de Notre Dame.
</P>
<P>
Also on display are stylized paintings of many inhabited
bridges, a type of bridge that flourished in Europe between the
12th and 18th centuries and still fires the imagination of
architects today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is jointly organized by the Urban Council and
the British Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
