<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Late Leader Ye Jianying  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today lauded late State leader Ye Jianying at a meeting marking
the 100th anniversary of his birth.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Ye Jianying was a long-tested faithful soldier to
communism, a staunch Marxist, a great proletarian revolutionary,
statesman and military strategist. He was among the founders of
the People's Liberation Army and the People's Republic of China,
and an outstanding leader who for a long period of time held
important positions in the government and the military," Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
In his revolutionary career of 60-odd years Ye made great
contributions to the Chinese people's cause of liberation and
socialist construction, and thereby won the esteem and respect of
the whole Party, the military forces and the Chinese people, the
president added.
</P>
<P>
When he was a young man Ye engaged in pursuing truth and saving
the nation and people, and threw himself into the democratic
revolution led by Sun Yet-Sen to fight against warlords and the
reactionary forces, Jiang told the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ye also participated in the founding of the Whampoa Military
Academy and the Northern Expedition (1926-1927), which was part of
the First Revolutionary Civil War (1924-1927) waged by the Chinese
people under the leadership of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
against the imperialists and the Northern warlords, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
At the critical moment when Chiang Kai-shek and Wang Jingwei
betrayed the revolution in 1927, resulting in the deaths of a
large number of communists, Ye published an open telegram
denouncing Chiang and joined the CPC, thereby evolving into a
communist from a patriotic democrat, the president noted.
</P>
<P>
From that time on he became entirely dedicated to Communism and
fought for it for the rest of his life, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Ye Jianying made glorious achievements for the
realization of the independence of the Chinese nation and the
liberation of the Chinese people," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the White-terror days after the initial failure of the
revolution he resolutely supported and coordinated the
preparations for the August 1 Nanchang Uprising (1927), which
fired the first shot against the Kuomintang (KMT) reactionaries
and marked the beginning of the CPC's independent leadership of
the revolutionary war. Ye also participated in leading the
Guangzhou Uprising (December 11, 1927).
</P>
<P>
The two uprisings and the Autumn Harvest Uprising marked the
great beginning of the Second Revolutionary Civil War (1927-1933)
and the establishment of the the people's army.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Late Leader Ye Jianying (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Central Soviet Area, established during the second
Revolutionary Civil War, Ye supported the correct line of Comrade
Mao Zedong and participated in the command of three
counter-"sieges" against the KMT troops led by Chiang Kai-shek.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the Long March, Ye resolutely upheld the unity
of the whole Party and the military, and wisely and bravely fought
against Zhang Guotao's conspiracy to split the Red Army and
endanger the CPC Central Committee, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang quoted Mao as saying that Comrade Ye "saved the Party and
the Red Army" at that critical moment.
</P>
<P>
After the Red Army reached northern Shaanxi Province at the end
of the Long March, Ye did a great deal for the establishment and
development of the Party's national united front against the Japanese
invaders, the president pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He assisted Zhou Enlai to bring about a peaceful settlement of
the Xi'an Incident (December 12, 1936), which resulted in a second
period of cooperation between the CPC and the KMT against Japanese
aggression, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Following the outbreak of the War Against Japanese Aggression
in 1937, Ye went on to take part in the Party's leading work in
Nanjing, Wuhan, Changsha, Chongqing and other places.
</P>
<P>
After he returned to the military headquarters in Yan'an, Ye
assisted Mao Zedong and Zhu De to command the campaigns against
Japanese invaders. After victory was won Ye assisted Zhou Enlai to
negotiate with the KMT for an agreement to end the civil
war. Later, he struggled against the KMT and exposed the true
motive of the KMT authorities in sabotaging the talks and
continuing the civil war. During the period of China's War of
Liberation (1945-1949), Ye led the rear-area work of the CPC
Central Committee in northwest Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Ye did a great deal for the peaceful liberation of Beijing,
commanded the campaign to liberate Guangdong Province and the
island of Hainan, and eventually won final victory on the South
China battlefield, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Ye performed immortal historical feats for the victory
of the Chinese revolution, the president noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0063 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Late Leader Ye Jianying (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After New China was founded in 1949, Ye Jianying made important
contributions to the cause of socialist revolution and
construction, the president said. The tasks of wiping out bandits,
land reform, building of people's political power, and
rehabilitation and promotion of production, were victoriously
accomplished when he presided over the routine work in south China
and central-south China areas.
</P>
<P>
He held a leading position in the Central Military Commission
from 1954, and creatively put Mao Zedong's military thinking into
practice. He was in charge of organizing the army's education and
training and developing military-related scientific and
technological research, and made great achievements in building up
a modern and regular army, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
During the "cultural revolution" (1966-1976), He fought against
the cliques headed by Lin Biao and Jiang Qing and made every
effort to maintain the army's and nation's stability, as well as
to resist and rectify the mistakes of the "cultural revolution",
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Ye, joined by other central leaders, toppled the Gang
of Four in 1976, in accordance with the will of the Party and
people. He played a decisive part in the struggle, the success of
which saved the Party and the nation from disaster. He strongly
demanded that Deng Xiaoping, Chen Yun and some other veteran
revolutionaries resume their leading posts in the Party and the
State, in spite of objections, the president said.
</P>
<P>
Ye gave full support to the reform and opening-up policy
initiated by Deng Xiaoping as well as the modernization drive. The
building of democracy and the legal system was greatly enhanced
when he was in charge of the National People's Congress, and the
Message To Compatriots in Taiwan was passed in January 1979. He
put forward nine principles for peaceful reunification of the
motherland in a famous speech made in September 1981. He was an
principal member of the Party's second generation's collective
leadership with Deng Xiaoping at the core, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Late Leader Ye Jianying (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ye was a staunch Communist and was always loyal to the Party
and the people. He always bore the interests of the Party and
people in mind in times of severe test. He stepped forward
bravely to turn the tide at crucial moments in Chinese
revolutionary history. Mao Zedong and Zhou Enlai spoke highly of
him in this regard, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He had largeness of mind and never claimed credit for himself. He
kept on studying Marxist theory in his late years and believed in
seeking truth from facts. He wrote many poems, and was held in
high esteem as a poet by Mao Zedong himself.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the Party, the Chinese people put
an end to the miserable history of Old China, and are marching
forward along the road of socialism with Chinese
characteristics. "Mao Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and other veteran
revolutionaries have passed away, but their great achievements,
precious thinking, lofty morals and noble spirit will be
everlasting, and encourage us to make even greater progress,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We should carry out their behests and accomplish their
unfinished cause in honoring Ye and other veterans who have passed
away. We will stick to the Party's basic line and Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics in
further promoting the reform and opening-up policies and the
modernization drive," the president said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
