<HEADLINE> Steffi Graf to Return to Tennis in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Germany's top star Steffi Graf
will return to tennis in May after a three-month pause to heal an
injured knee.
</P>
<P>
The former world number one will take part in a May 12-18 WTA
tournament in Berlin, tournament director Eberhard Wensky said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Graf, 27, was forced to withdraw with a left-knee tendon
infection at the Toray Pan Pacific Open in Tokyo on Feb. 2, where
she was to have faced Swiss 16-year-old Martina Hingis in the
final.
</P>
<P>
The infection also prevented Graf from playing in the Fed Cup,
where Germany lost to the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
But Hingis, who overtook Graf as the world No. 1 player on
March 30, won't play in Berlin. She is out with a knee injury
after a horse-riding spill a week ago and said she hopes to be fit
for the French Open starting May 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
