<HEADLINE> EU Approves Aid for Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) said
today that it had approved a humanitarian aid package of 3.7
million ECUs (4.2 million U.S. dollars) for victims of conflict in
Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the EU's executive body, said the
priority would be to cover basic needs -- food and medical aid --
of the most vulnerable part of the population, in particular those
who have been displaced.
</P>
<P>
The aid, managed by the European Community Humanitarian Office
(ECHO), will enable Red Cross and non-governmental organizations
to carry out a program in the next eight months.
</P>
<P>
The office has scaled down its presence in Somalia over the
past two years as emergency needs have declined there. But it
said some humanitarian assistance was still vital, especially in
the capital of Mogadishu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
