<HEADLINE> 106 Zairean Government Soldiers Under Strict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and six Zairean
government troops are and will remain under strict guard in
Kitwe, Copperbelt Province of Zambia until they decide to go back
to Zaire.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by Copperbelt Deputy Minister Charles
Museba in Ndola, capital of the province, according to Zambia
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The 106 Zairean soldiers fled their country into Copperbelt
Province and Luapula Province after rebel leader Laurent Kabila's
troops took over Zaire's second largest city Lubumbashi earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Museba said that Zambia is not keeping the Zairean soldiers
under hostage as they have decided on their own to travel to
Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
