<HEADLINE> Italy to Reschedule Uganda's Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Italy is to reschedule Uganda's
debt owed to the west European country.
</P>
<P>
According to the Italian embassy source here today, Uganda
owes Italy 68 million U.S. dollars and Italy will reduce the
interest on the loan and extend the period for its repayment for
another 20 or 30 years.
</P>
<P>
The source said that Italy will give Uganda a grant of 19
million dollars for humanitarian and developmental projects
following the visit of the Italian minister of state for foreign
affairs in charge of development cooperation, Rino Serri who
arrived in Uganda yesterday in a bid to strengthen bilateral
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Serri will also hold discussions with Ugandan high-ranking
officials on the settlement of the Great Lake region crisis.
</P>
<P>
Italy holds that Uganda is a key country in the region,
persisting in the fact that it is impossble to see stability in
Africa without involving Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
