<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended the
day slightly higher, buoyed by comments from the Reserve Bank of
Australia (RBA) restating its strong commitment to low inflation.
</P>
<P>
It closed at 77.74 U.S. cents compared with a close at 77.30
last session.
</P>
<P>
"RBA deputy governor Stephen Grenville's comments, reinforcing
the central bank's focus on low inflation, had led to buying of
the local currency in the middle of the day," IBJ foreign exchange
dealer Steve Chater said.
</P>
<P>
The comments were interpreted as suggesting that the RBA would
not reduce interest rates in the coming months.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar closed mostly higher.
It ended the day at 98.56 Japanese yen from 98.32 and at 1.3469
German marks from 1.3428.  
</P>
</TEXT>
