<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portuguese President Visits Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese President Jorge
Sampaio arrived here today to start his six-day state visit to
Mozambique at the invitation of President Joaquim Chissano.
</P>
<P>
President Sampaio is schedulled to hold talks later today with
his host President Chissano, parliamentary leaders and Afonso
Dhlakama, leader of Mozambique's biggest opposition National
Resistance Movement.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese president and his delegation including 15
ministers and secretary of state will also visit Beira City, Tete
and Nampula provinces.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving for Mozambique, Sampaio has said that his visit
was aimed at strengthening friendship and cooperation between the
two countries and promoting Portugal's investment in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Portugal is the biggest foreign investor in Mozambique,
accounting for 26 percent of a total of 1.5 billion US Dollars
foreign investment in this country so far. 
