dragged lower today as investors remained cautious ahead of key
data due out both here and in the United States this week.
</P>
<P>
Shares dropped at the open, weighed down by New York's poor
finish on Friday, and continued in negative territory, with little
news to provide momentum.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index shed 13 points to finish at 2,461.7.
</P>
<P>
