<HEADLINE> Food Rations for Iraqis to Be Increased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Food supplies will be
distributed throughout Iraq in accordance with new rations as
from next month, an Iraqi Trade Ministry spokesman announced
today.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency (INA) quoted the spokesman as saying
that the new rations were set in the light of the amounts of food
supplies imported in accordance with the memorandum of
understanding signed between Iraq with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The monthly food supply rations per capita will be as
follows: nine kilograms of wheat, 2.5 kilograms of rice, one
kilogram of vegetable oil, 350 grams of washing powder, 250
grams of soap, one kilogram of legumes, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 2.7 kilograms of infant milk will be offered to
children per head, the spokesman explained.
</P>
<P>
The per capita food supply by the Trade Ministry to the Iraqis
in the past months rationed monthly was seven kilograms of wheat,
1.25 kilograms of rice, 750 grams of vegetable oil and 1.8
kilograms of infant milk.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman affirmed that the new food supply rations will
be enforced despite the obstacles put by the U.S. in blocking the
approval by the U.N. Sanctions Committee of a number of contracts
signed by Iraq with foreign suppliers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
