<HEADLINE> DPR Korea Sails into Women's Team Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic
People's Republic of Korea whitewashed South Korea in the women's
team semi-finals at the World Table Tennis Championships here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
DPR Korea, which had skipped the previous two championships,
lived up to its dark-horse billing by handing a straight-game
defeat to South Korea, runner-up at the last Worlds.
</P>
<P>
Kim Hyon Hui, quarter-finalist in the Olympic Games last
summer, put DPR Korea ahead with a 14-21, 21-9, 22-20 victory over
Ryu Ji Hye. Wi Bok Sun made it 2-0 after routing South Korean Kim
Moo Kyo 21-19, 21-11 in the second rubber.
</P>
<P>
Wi Bok Sun completed the victory with a 21-17, 19-21, 21-18
triumph over South Korean top player Park Hae Jung.
</P>
<P>
DPR Korea is to take on winner of the other semi-final between
defending world champion China and European champion Germany on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea and DPR Korea formed a joint team in the 1991 world
championships in Chiba, Japan, where they edged out China 3-2 in
the final. 
