<HEADLINE> Exhibits Show Artistic Link Between China and France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A fine collection of 147 works
of art was shown in Hong Kong today highlighting the artistic
interaction between China and France.
</P>
<P>
Most of the exhibits are selected from the Guimet National
Museum of Asiatic Arts, one of the museums renowned for its Asian
art collection. The art objects on display include enamels,
porcelains, paintings and engravings ranging from 2 B.C. to 1,800
A.D.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the Guimet collection, important loans from Louvre
Museum, the Chateau of Versailles, the French National Library and
the National Archives are also added to the exhibition, entitled
"From Beijing to Versailles: Artistic Relations between China and
France".
</P>
<P>
Half of the exhibits are arranged to provide a historical
overview of the three periods -- the Silk Route, the Mongols and
Islam, and the Church and the King, and the other half demonstrate
three artistic forms -- engraving, painting and the decorative
art.
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by the Consulate General of France in Hong
Kong and the Urban Council, the exhibition will last through June
15.  
</P>
</TEXT>
