<HEADLINE> Nigeria Airways to Resume Flight to London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's national flag carrier,
the Nigeria Airways is soon to resume its Lagos-London flight
after a month's suspension due to insurance debt, the Guardian
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at the end of a week-long meeting
between the airline, the National Insurance Corporation of
Nigeria and the Ministry of Aviation.
</P>
<P>
The British Civil Aviation Authority banned Nigeria Airways
from flying its Lagos-London flight in early March due to alleged
irregularities in its insurance papers.
</P>
<P>
The National Insurance Corporation of Nigeria also decided to
dump the Alexander Howden and Co., which is involved in the
insurance fraud and has chosen Johnson Higgins and Co. as its new
partner, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, Nigeria Airways is also engaged in
talks for the re-opening of the Lagos-New York route before the
third quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
Preparations are also being done for the opening of the
Lagos-Jeddh-Dubai and the Port Harcourt-Dubai routes, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria airways has abandoned most of its international
flights for a long time due to serious mismanagement and
financial difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
