<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Develops Economic Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- LNnet, an economic information
network covering Northeast China's Liaoning Province, went into
operation today.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first network of its kind in the northeastern
part of the country.
</P>
<P>
LNnet is a key part of the nationwide China Economic
Information Network (CEInet), jointly set up by the State
Information Center, provincial information centers and the
information centers of various ministries.
</P>
<P>
It cost the province about 100 million yuan to build.
</P>
<P>
CEInet provides economic information about China to the
country's governmental organizations, enterprises and private
users, and it is hooked up to the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that CEInet will help add China-developed economic
information to the Internet, which is badly short of such
information, to promote the country's information development as
part of the country's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
LNnet was jointly constructed by the Information Center of
Liaoning Province, and other local information institutes.
</P>
<P>
It will not only provide a variety of economic information in
the fields of macro-economic development, industrial and commercial
surveys, and business opportunities, but also services,
such as e-mail and information retrieval.  
</P>
</TEXT>
