<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 11:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Following are business briefs from
the Middle East countries:
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The contract for the United Arab Emirates' (UAE)
first satellite, the Thuraya mobile satellite, will be awarded in
a few months, an UAE official in charge of the project told Xinhua
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, to be launched before the year 2000, is the
first of its kind in the Middle East region and the fifth in the
world, said Jamal Al Jarwan, Marketing Manger of Emirates
Telecommunications Corporation (Etisalat).
</P>
<P>
The project was initiated by the Etisalat which opened tenders
for four international companies, including Alcatel Telecom and
Aeronautic of France and Hughes and Lockheed of the United States,
at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
"We are still in evaluation stage and the selection of
the successful bidder is expected in the third quarter of 1997",
the official said.
</P>
<P>
The Etisalat is the biggest shareholder of the project, owning
20 percent of the total shares while the rest are owned by other
Arab investors.
</P>
<P>
The project, worth between 700 million to one billion
U.S. dollars, could include two satellites covering the Middle
East, Eastern Europe, North Africa, Central Asia and the Arabian
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Japanese financial assistance to Jordan for the fiscal
year 1997-98 will amount to 200 million U.S. dollars, Jordanian
newspaper Al-Dustour reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Japanese ambassador to Jordan Takayoko Kimora
as saying that the assistance would be given in the form of soft
loans, loans with grace periods, expertise and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Kimora added that his country looks forward to having closer
ties with Jordan and supporting it economically.
</P>
<P>
Japan's fiscal year starts in April every year and its
foreign assistance programs are determined in the same month.
</P>
<P>
EGYPT -- Egyptian Minister of Tourism Mamdouh el-Beltagui has
approved 3 million U.S. dollars as preliminary budget to
finance media campaign to promote Egypt's tourist activity through
U.S. Cable News Network (CNN).
</P>
<P>
Tourist experts are expecting Egypt to receive more than 4 million
tourists this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the hotel capacity in Egypt will
increase by 200,000 rooms during the next three to five years.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that 286 tourist projects were approved in
January 1996 till February 1997.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- A large Iraqi trade and industrial delegation
comprising officials from the Ministry of Trade and the Chambers
of Commerce and Industry Federations left for Ankara Sunday on a
week-long visit to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Delegation sources said in pre-departure statements that they
will hold talks with the Turkish side on ways to foster bilateral
trade and industrial ties and reactivate trade exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
