<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Judge Sentences Cop to 450 Years in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (Xinhua) -- A Brazilian judge today
sentenced a former policeman to almost 450 years in prison for
killing 21 residents in a slum here.
</P>
<P>
Paulo Roberto Alvarenga, 38, who was one of the 52 policemen
accused of a role in the 1993 massacre, described by prosecutors
as revenge for the deaths of four policemen presumable killed by
drug traffickers in the slum.
</P>
<P>
Alvarenga was sentenced for 21 homicides and on four counts of
attempted murder by Judge Jose Antonio.
</P>
<P>
Under Brazilian law, however, Alvarenga can not serve more than
30 years. But the symbolic 450 years of imprisonment was still
seen as a positive sign for the dozens of more trials to follow.
</P>
</TEXT>
