<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Political, Economic Confidence in HK Steady: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Public confidence in Hong
Kong's political and economic outlook remained steady with only
60-odd days left before the handover, a poll showed.
</P>
<P>
The overall economic confidence index was kept at 93 points,
the same as that recorded three months ago, while the political
confidence index dropped just one point to 94 points.
</P>
<P>
The quarterly confidence poll has been conducted since January
1985 by the Survey Research Hongkong (SRH) for two local
newspapers -- Ming Pao and South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
The poll also showed that the major intention purchase index
surged from 84 to 91 points, with more respondents indicating
their intentions to buy housing estates, cars, furniture or other
high-valued items in near future.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, more than half the respondents -- 57 percent --
expected Hong Kong to be as prosperous as it was now and one
quarter believed that it would be more prosperous.
</P>
<P>
From April 7 to 11 SRH polled 1,075 respondents between the
ages of 15 and 64, to produce the last edition of the indices
before the handover.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
