<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Rate Falls Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Continuing its downward slide,
India's annual rate of inflation dropped 0.35 percentage points to
6.64 percent for the week ending April 12, the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, inflation was around 4.85 percent during the
corresponding week in April last year.
</P>
<P>
