<HEADLINE> 4th South Asia Travel, Tourism Exchange Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- South Asia "Travel Mart", the
fourth South Asian Travel and Tourism Exchange (SATTE) Conference,
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the conference is "Coming Together - Peace and
Prosperity Through Tourism."
</P>
<P>
The conference was inaugurated by Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga with over 500 regional and international
travel and tour operators attending the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Minister of Media, Tourism and Aviation Dharmasiri
Senanayake said at the ceremony that the theme of the meeting is
very appropriate and timely in view of the necessity for Asian
nations to come closer for better understanding and sharing of the
available markets.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out, "Peace is vital to promote tourism. Let us
strive together to achieve peace not only in our respective
countries but also in the region as well."
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the meeting is to implement matters
pertaining to the development of travel and tourism in the region.
Mutual interest and the larger topic of making the entire South
Asian region a more important tourism destination, as well as the
development of intra-regional tourism are among the subjects to be
discussed at the meeting, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The SATTE, which started in 1994, is an initial step in
developing the South Asia region as a destination in the
international market place and the further strengthening of
intra-regional travel among South Asian countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
