<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-chairwoman Meets Laotian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua)-- Chen Muhua, vice-chairwoman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), met
with a Laotian prosecution delegation led by Ounla Xayasane,
prosecutor-general of the Supreme People's Prosecution Office of
Laos, in the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
China and Laos are friendly neighbors, Chen said, adding that
the strengthening of exchange and cooperation between the two
countries in judicial and other areas would help enhance mutual
understanding and be conducive to promoting the traditional
friendship between the two people and the relationship as a whole
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chen briefed the visitors on the legislative work of the NPC
and its Standing Committee, on the legal framework for the
country's socialist market economy in particular, and supervision
of the enforcement of laws.
</P>
<P>
The Laotian visitors arrived here Sunday as guests of China's
Supreme People's Procuratorate. During his talks with Zhang
Siqing, Procurator-general of China's Supreme People's
Procuratorate, this morning on strengthening exchanges between
attorneys of the two countries, Xayasane said China's progress in
building up its legal system is worth studying by Laos.
</P>
<P>
The Laotian delegation is also scheduled to visit Nanjing,
Shanghai, and Yunnan during its stay in China.  
</P>
