<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index declined 22.81 points to close at 1996.79 points today,
breading through the psychological resistance line of 2000 points.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to a new thin level of 66.32 million
units, valued at 239.34 million Singapore dollars (about 166.21
million U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 242 to 49,
while 329 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Sin Soon Huat was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 45.93 million units. It was followed by
the Singapore Telecom which had 5.97 million shares traded. The
Kuala Lumpur Ind. was next with 2.47 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose 1.2 Singapore
dollars to finish at 21.5 Singapore dollars. Samanda Holdings
increased 30 cents to end at 9.4 Singapore dollars, while the
Asean Fund closed 20 cents higher at 16.3 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local property developer City Developments and
the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign shared the top spot on the
list as each fell 70 cents to close at 12 and 13.4 Singapore
dollars respectively. Malaya Banking was 60 cents lower at 14.6
dollars, while F&AMP;N lost 50 cents to end at 10.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
