<HEADLINE> Japanese Government Regrets at Visit to Diaoyu Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government expressed
regret today at an unauthorized visit to China's Diaoyu Islands in
the East China Sea by a Japanese reporter and a local official,
Kyodo News Service reported.
</P>
<P>
"It is a regrettable thing," Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary
Teijiro Furukawa was quoted by the news service as saying.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Maritime Safety Agency said the reporter from Sankei
Shimbon, a Tokyo-based newspaper, and an assemblyman from the city
of Ishigaki landed from a boat on one of the islets of the Diaoyu
Islands around 12:30 p.m. Sunday, and left it 45 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Furukawa said that Maritime Safety Agency officials explained
relevant laws to the two men and asked them to abide by the law,
but the advice was ignored, according to Kyodo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
