<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Debt Hits 116.28 Billion US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China borrowed 30.95 billion US
dollars from overseas in 1996, bringing its total outstanding
foreign debt up to 116.28 billion US dollars last year, according
to the latest statistics from the State Administration of Foreign
Exchange (SAFE).
</P>
<P>
The figure was up 9.69 billion US dollars, or 9.1 percent from
the previous year, said the SAFE.
</P>
<P>
Medium- and long-term loans, at 102.17 billion US dollars last
year, accounted for 87.9 percent of the total amount, up 7.49
billion US dollars or 7.9 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The short-term foreign loans rose 2.19 billion US dollars, or
18.4 percent over 1995 to reach 14.11 billion US dollars in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
