<HEADLINE> 125 Students Arrested for Involving Campus Violence in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A total of 125 students of Rajshahi
University were arrested in a police swoop Sunday and 90 of them
were sued for their alleged involvement in the ransacking of
various university buildings last Saturday, said reports reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
Besides, some off-campus student messes and houses in the
nearby villages were also raided by the law enforcers of the
Rajshahi district, 200 kilometers northwest of the capital Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The police raid happened after a serious campus violence last
Saturday, when at least 60 people were injured in an armed attack
by some students belonging to the so-called shibir, a student wing
of this country's opposition party Jamaat-e-Islami.
</P>
<P>
The violence erupted when the shibir activists called a strike
from Saturday demanding reinstating former vice-chancellor Yousuf
Ali and cancellation of the newly-introduced department-wise
admission system.
</P>
<P>
According to the university authorities, the pro-strike
students disconnected the telephone lines of the new
vice-chancellor's residence as well as the residence of teachers
and officers. They also attacked the university employees and the
police.
</P>
<P>
Local police sources said that 35 of the arrested people were
released later as they were found not involved in last Saturday's
incident.
</P>
<P>
The police has been posted on the campus to maintain law and
order while the university was closed till June 10 for the summer
vacation, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
