<HEADLINE> Hospitalized Peng Zhen Visited by Chinese Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Communist Party and
government leaders had gone to the hospital to visit Peng Zhen,
China's outstanding leader, who died of illness on the night of
April 26.
</P>
<P>
Peng Zhen was a great proletarian revolutionary and statesman,
an outstanding activist in state affairs, a staunch Marxist, a
principal founder of the socialist legal system in China and an
outstanding leader of the Party and the state.
</P>
<P>
When Peng Zhen was in a critical condition, Party and
government leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu
Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren went to the hospital
to visit Peng or extended their regards in other forms.
</P>
