<HEADLINE> China's Community Services Benefit Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of community
services are benefitting citizens of Southwest China's Sichuan
province who are in difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials say that the region began to provide
community services in 1987, to help the elderly, disabled people,
poor families, or any residents who are in trouble.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 20,000 service centers have been set up in the province,
with more than 60,000 community volunteers.
</P>
<P>
With the help of local young volunteers, more than 50,000 poor
families reportedly have said good-bye to poverty, and nearly
30,000 laid-off workers have found new jobs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
