<HEADLINE> Syrian, Egyptian Presidents Exchanges Views on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
and his Egyptian counterpart Hosni Mubarak has exchanged views on
the latest developments of the stalled Middle East peace process,
Damascus radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The exchanges of views between the two presidents came Sunday
night in a telephone call from Mubarak to Assad, who frequently
coordinate stances towards the peace march.
</P>
<P>
According to Damascus radio, the two presidents exchanged
views on the inter-Arab contacts which are being conducted to meet
the challenges facing the Arabs and their national issues.
</P>
<P>
The telephone contact between the two leaders came following a
visit by the Egyptian president to Saudi Arabia and Kuwait, during
which he discussed with Saudi and Kuwaiti leaders the current
developments of the Middle East peace process, in addition to a
number of Arab and international issues.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process has been stalled because of
the Israeli government's intransigence in constructing a Jewish
settlement in Har Home in Arab East Jerusalem. 
</P>
