<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Improving Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Animal husbandry, a leading part
of agriculture in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region,
has developed well over the last several years.
</P>
<P>
The region had 34 billion yuan in output value from the sector
last year, a 26 percent rise over the previous year, and it
contributed more than a third of the total output value from local
agriculture and helped local farmers substantially increase their
incomes.
</P>
<P>
Last year the local meat output was more than 2.9 million tons,
egg output was 153,000 tons, and milk 9,000 tons, meaning
increases of 18, 5, and 4 percent, respectively, from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
The increases come from restructuring the sector and improving
management, livestock strains, breeding methods, and veterinary
services.
</P>
<P>
Now Priority is being given to poultry, sheep, and rabbit
breeding, which has grown faster than pig raising. The region has
also done well in improving pig and cattle breeds, and building
lean-meat pig production bases.
</P>
<P>
Local livestock breeding has become more intensive and
industrialized, and there is a growing number of households and
villages specializing in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The region aims to have 42 billion yuan in output value from
the sector this year by producing 3.1 million tons of meat,
163,000 tons of eggs, and 9,400 tons of milk.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970428.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 09:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Niger's President Arrives in Kuwait on Three-day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The President of Niger,
Ibrahim Barre Mainassara, arrived here today for a three-day
official visit during which he will held talks with Kuwaiti
Amir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah on bilateral economic and
political cooperations.
</P>
<P>
The west African republic is among many world countries that
have supported Kuwait's efforts to enforce Iraq's full compliance
with the UN Security Council resolutions concerning the Iraqi
invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Niger's former Prime Minister Ahmoud Shifo visited Kuwait in
1992 and held talks with Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime
Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah on bilateral relations
and other issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
Niger's Foreign Minister Mohamed Bazoum visited Kuwait in
November 1995.
</P>
<P>
In April 1992, former Kuwaiti Minister of State for
Municipal Affairs Ibrahim Al-Shain inaugurated in Niger an
Islamic Center donated by Kuwaiti Amir which included a
school, a health center and a mosque worth 1.2 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti Fund for Arab Economic Development established in
1961 is partly financing seven development projects in the
sectors of agriculture, electricity, water and economic plan
program in Niger totaling 61 million U.S. dollars, official
Kuwait News Agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
