<HEADLINE> Power Plants Aid Power Industry in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Since 1994 power plants in other
parts of the country have provided funding and materials for the
Tibet Autonomous Region to boost its power industry.
</P>
<P>
Energy shortages in Tibet constitute a major factor holding
back local economic development. Since 1994, 49.4 million yuan of
funds has been raised by power plants in other parts of
the country to upgrade power grids in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Bank also extended 48.6 million yuan in
loans to aid the upgrading and expansion of the existing power
grids in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
During the past three years, some 102 experts have also been
sent to train workers and technicians in the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
