<HEADLINE> Rockwell Donates 400,000 yuan to Chinese Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The US-based Rockwell
International has donated 400,000 yuan (about 48,000 US dollars)
to the Shanghai Children's Medical Center for the purchase of
medical equipment.
</P>
<P>
The money was presented to the center by Project Hope, an
international non-profit organization that conducts medical
training programs around the world.
</P>
<P>
The medical center is being constructed by the Shanghai No.2
Medical University and Project Hope, and is expected to be the
largest pediatric hospital, as well as a training center, in the
country when it goes into operation next year.
</P>
<P>
It is designed to be able to provide medical service to 250,000
children annually.
</P>
<P>
Project Hope has trained more than 13 million medical workers
across the world since it was founded in US in 1958. 
