<HEADLINE> 10 of A Family Killed in Fatal Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Ten people of a same family
were killed when a speedy bus turned turtle near Gujrat in
Gujranwala district, Punjab province, early this morning.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, the
bus was packed with dozens of people who were returning from a
wedding party. The bus driver lost control of the vehicle due to
excessive speed.
</P>
<P>
Six people were reported to be killed on the spot, while the
injured were rushed to a local hospital, where four others
succumbed to their injuries. The dead included four children.
</P>
<P>
The 10 people killed belong to a same family, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver, the bridegroom, his parents and the bride are
in a critical condition. The bridal couple are reported to have
lost their arms in the tragic incident.  
</P>
