<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
drifted lower today in quiet trading.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 14 points lower at 2240 with a turnover
of only 28 million NZ dollars (19 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The market was dragged down by a 10-cent fall in the market
leader Telecom, whose shares finished at 643 cents, with the
company's US-listed ADRs weaker over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Lion Nathan shares fell 6 cents to 342 cents after reporting a
20.8 percent drop in its profit to February 28 compared with the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the other losers, Air New Zealand dipped 3 cents to 284
cents, Brierley Investment were also down 3 cents to 126 cents,
and Fletcher Building slipped 1 cents to 407 cents.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey went against the weaker trend, rising 6
cents to 317 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 28 rises and 55 falls.  
