<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Belarus Presidents Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great importance
to developing economic and trade ties with Belarus on the basis of
equality and mutual benefit, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Belarus President Aleksandr Lukashenko, who
stopped over in Beijing on his way home, Jiang said China is
willing to explore new ways and fields to further bilateral
cooperation and to promote various forms of mutually beneficial
cooperation between the countries' enterprises according to the
international trade norms.
</P>
<P>
During the one-hour meeting, both Jiang and Lukashenko
expressed their satisfaction over the progress of the bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to Lukashenko on his third visit to China,
Jiang spoke highly of the Belarus leader's important contributions
to the Sino-Belarus friendship and mutually beneficial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the bilateral ties have enjoyed a smooth and healthy
development since the establishment of the diplomatic relations
between the two countries five years ago.
</P>
<P>
It has been the important guarantee for the steady development
that leaders of the two countries have maintained constant
contacts and forged a good relationship of mutual understanding
and trust, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President said that the political document signed
by leaders of the two countries has laid a legal basis for
promoting bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Facts have proved that the Sino-Belarus ties have withstood the
test of changing international situations, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko thanked Jiang and the Chinese government for their
efforts to promote the bilateral relations, saying the friendly
links between the two peoples are expanding through the joint
efforts of both sides.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said that the bilateral cooperative relationship has
good prospects.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also briefed his Belarus counterpart on his just-ended
visit to Russia, which he described as "very successful."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said: "Russian President Boris Yeltsin and I signed the
joint statement on the world's multipolarization and on
establishment of a new world order. This is an important document."
</P>
<P>
"We deem that following the Cold War, the world's
multipolarization has been gaining momentum and the proposition
for a unipolar world just won't work. All countries have the right
to choose independently their own path of development according to
their national conditions and no country should force its own
social system and values on others," Jiang elaborated.
</P>
<P>
The current world is diversified and colorful, and all
countries should join hands to take their share, on an equal
footing, in solving problems relating to world peace and
development, Jiang stressed, adding one cannot lay down the law
for international affairs alone.
</P>
<P>
"In these fields, China and Belarus share wide-ranging common
grounds," he stated.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko also briefed Jiang on his country's political and
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China has always respected and understood
Belarus's path of development in compliance with its own
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, both sides also exchanged views on
furthering cooperation in all other fields.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion were: Chinese Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing, Minister Bao Xuding of Machine-Building Industry,
Minister Wu Yi of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation,
Vice-Minister Zhang Deguang of Foreign Affairs, Deputy Chief Qian
Shugen of the General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army.
</P>
<P>
P. Shipuk, Chairman of House of Republics of the National
Assembly of Belarus, P. Prokopovich, First Deputy Prime Minister,
and I. Antonovich, Minister of Foreign Affairs, were also
present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
