<P>
NINGBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An Ocean Shipping Institute has
been set up at Ningbo University, in Ningbo City, Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
The institute has more than 280 staff members and students and
consists of two departments, three research institutes, six
faculty offices, and 26 labs.
</P>
<P>
The institute will cooperate with the East China Fleet of the
Chinese navy for teaching purposes.
</P>
<P>
Two Hong Kong businessmen originally from Ningbo have donated
four million yuan to the new institute to build a navigation
building. 
</P>
