<HEADLINE> BSEC Business Conference Opens in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A conference of the Black Sea
Economic Cooperation (BSEC) of "Opportunities for Business" began
today in Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Participants are expected to discuss the issues of regional
cooperation, economic rebuilding, financing for growth and
investment projects, telecommunications, agriculture and
transportation during the three-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Heads of state from Azerbaijan, Armenia, Georgia, Moldovia,
Ukraine, Romania and Turkey are expected to attend the conference.
</P>
<P>
Besides participating in the conference, Romanian President
Emil Constantinescu will also pay an official visit to Turkey on
the sidelines of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian president will proceed to Ankara, capital of
Turkey, to hold official talks with the Turkish side on
bilateral ties as well as regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
The BSEC, formed in 1992, is an 11-nation regional pact that
groups Turkey, Greece, Bulgaria, Albania, Romania and six former
Soviet republics. It is aimed at cooperating in transport,
energy, telecommunications, science and technology, industry,
tourism, economic data and statistics, agriculture, and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
It aslo seeks to remove barriers of trade and facilitate the
travel of businessmen among the members states. 
</P>
