<HEADLINE> China's First Work on Flood And Drought Disasters Comes Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- "Flood And Drought Disasters in
Yellow River Valley" has recently been published by the Yellow
River Water Conservancy Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
As China's first scientific, systematic overview of flood and
drought disasters, the book supplies materials and data of ancient
and contemporary floods and droughts.
</P>
<P>
From perspectives of nature and society, the book analyses the
factors influencing the disasters, reveals the regular disaster
pattern of the Yellow River valley, and gives some methods to
prevent the occurrences and reduce the losses.
</P>
<P>
Some experts and scholars have said that the book gives a
series of new opinions, and has both academic and practical
value. The Chinese Ministry of Water Conservancy has organized
scientific appraisement of the book.  
</P>
