<HEADLINE> Palestinian Youth Killed by Israeli Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An 18-year-old Palestinian
youth was shot dead by Israeli soldiers in the West Bank Sunday
night, according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press
service based in East Jerusalem today.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place in the Village of Tharaz near Hebron
when young Palestinian stone-throwers clashed with Israeli
troops. The boy, named Issam Aqadneh, was killed on the spot and
two other Palestinian youths were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli troops began shooting after the youths in the
village blocked the main road with rocks and metal rods and
threw stones and petrol bombs at patrol jeeps.
</P>
<P>
The boy's funeral was carried out late Sunday night. Thousands
of the villagers shouted anti-Israeli and pro-Hamas slogans.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers in the occupied territories have grown ever
more trigger-happy since last month when a suicide bombing
occurred at a Tel Aviv cafe killing three Israeli women and the
bomber.
</P>
<P>
They were also instructed to step up security activities to
ensure the safety of Israeli holiday makers during the Jewish
Passover festival on April 22-28.
</P>
<P>
However, two Israeli women were found dead in Wadi Kelt in
the West Bank Friday. The two, identified as Hagit Zavitzky and
Liat Kastiel, were both 23 years old.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Police suspected the murders of the two women
hikers, whose bodies were found with multiple stab wounds, were
committed by Palestinian extremists. But criminal possibility is
also not entirely ruled out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
