<HEADLINE> New Hydropower Station Completed in Northern Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A hydropower station has gone into
operation in Nagqu Prefecture in northern Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Nagqu was one of China's last two prefectures which had no
access to hydropower electricity, relying only on small amounts of
geothermal energy and diesel power.
</P>
<P>
The power project was launched in April 1993 with allocations
from the central government. Located 4,350 m above sea level, the
station has four generation units, with a total capacity of 10,800
kw.
</P>
<P>
Despite the lack of oxygen and harsh construction conditions,
the army engineers completed the power station one year ahead of
schedule.  
</P>
