<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honey and Wax Production Below Expectations in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia produces only
25,000 tons of honey and 210 tons of wax every year despite the
fact that the country is one of the seven top honey and wax
producing countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by the Holeta Bee Research Center in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The center said actual performance is below expectations
because of backward bee keeping system.
</P>
<P>
According to the center, with modern bee keeping techniques,
it is possible to produce up to 140,000 tons of honey annually by
utilizing the currently available beehives in the country.
</P>
<P>
The center said it has produced modern beehives replacing
traditional ones with a plan to increase the production from 5 kg
to 20 kg per hive and the center is distributing the modern
beehives to rural technology promotion centers in addition to
offering training to farmers, professionals and other sector of
the society on modern bee keeping techniques.
</P>
<P>
The center added that the wax and honey produced in Ethiopia
have the quality to meet export standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
