<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Announces Income-tax-free Privileges to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority has announced that the government grants a 3-5 years
income-tax-free rights to entrepreneurs who engage in areas the
state gives particular attention to.
</P>
<P>
Among others, agriculture, horticulture and industrial
chemicals production are listed as the sectors paid special
attention by the government, the Ethiopian News Agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Investors who produce fertilizers as well as generate, store
and distribute electric power can import the necessary equipment
free of taxes, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Entrepreneurs who undertake investment activities within a 15
km radius of the Addis Ababa-Nazret Highway will be given a three
year income-tax-free privileges.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government grants similar privileges for five
years for investors engaging in the development of economically
backward regions such as Gambella, Benishangul-Gumuz, Somali and
Afar.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors with a capital of 500,000 US Dollars will be
relieved of income taxes for two years, said the authority.
</P>
