<HEADLINE> Chinese Customs Reports Sharp Increase In Telecom Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Customs office has
reported a sharp increase in imports of program-controlled
telephone exchange parts and accessories.
</P>
<P>
More than 15 million telephone exchanges have been installed
annually in China in recent years, increasing demand for parts and
accessories.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Customs, imported parts and
accessories in 1996 were valued at more than 91 million US
dollars, 4.7 times the 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
The momentum remains strong this year. In the first two months,
customs reported imports worth more than 49 million US dollars,
three times the amount in the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
State-run enterprises are the main importers, accounting for 44
million US dollars worth in the first two months, 3.3 times last
year's amount.
</P>
<P>
The products come mainly from Germany, Belgium, and Sweden, and
the rest from Canada, the United States and Australia. 
</P>
