<HEADLINE> Nepali Official Calls for Promotion of Internet Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A senior government official
has said Nepal should promote the use of the worldwide Internet to
make the rest of the world know about the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a talk program on "Internet in Information
Technology" here Sunday, State Minister for Information and
Communications Rakam Chemjong said the country needs to be
familiar with the use of the latest technology of communication,
otherwise it would be left far behind in the communications
sector.
</P>
<P>
The role of the computer-based communication network is
increasing in Nepal though many people here still don't know about
the Internet, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on those working in the field to strive to promote
the identity of Nepal through the web of the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Nepali users including travel agencies, tour operators and
local newspaper publishers have set up hundreds of home pages on
the Internet with a view to attracting foreign visitors and
disseminating news coverage about Nepal around the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
