<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Help Southwest China's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Overseas Chinese and compatriots
from Hongkong and Macao have provided more than 77 million US
dollars in foreign currency to support the economic growth of the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 3.2 million Guangxi people reported to be
living overseas, a number of whom have signed economic agreements
with the region.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, three joint projects were set up in three investment
and development zones in Guangxi, contributing more than 22
million US dollars in foreign currency.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities say that Guangxi set up three investment and
development zones for overseas Chinese business people in Nanning,
Guilin, and Chijiang last year. Their annual combined output value
reached 450 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Overseas Chinese are playing a very important role in the
region's effort to attract overseas investors. In 1996, they
helped as many as 80,000 overseas Chinese to contact and
cooperate with local enterprises.  
</P>
