<HEADLINE> North China Province to Introduce More Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
will import more technology to speed up the upgrading of its key
industries and promote its economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to introduce 2,500 items of advanced
technology annually over the next five years, 20 percent of which
is expected to generate more than half a million yuan in annual
taxes and profits each.
</P>
<P>
A majority of introduced technologies will used for upgrading
the farming sector, involving agricultural variety breeding, dry
farming, farm and sideline products processing, and aquaculture.
</P>
<P>
More emphasis will be placed on applying advanced technologies
to local hi-tech industries such as biology, electronics
information, new materials. energy, and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Hebei intends to cooperate with universities and hi-tech
research institutes in the neighboring municipalities of Beijing
and Tianjin and introduce scientific and technological findings
from the two municipalities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
