<HEADLINE> Indonesians Scale Mount Qomolangma on Nepal Side </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Indonesian climbers and two
Nepali mountaineering guides Saturday scaled the summit of the
world highest Mount Qomolangma through the southeast ridge on
Nepal side, according to the Tourism Ministry here.
</P>
<P>
The two Indonesian summitters are Misrin, 31, and Asmujino, 26,
the ministry said in a press release without giving their full
names.
</P>
<P>
The two men belongs to a 10-member Indonesian Qomolangma
expedition led by Iwan Setiwan, it added.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian woman climber Clara Sumarwati successfully climbed
the 8,848-meter-high mountain last September from the northern
side in China, becoming the first conquer of Mount Qomolangma from
the Southeast Asian region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
