<HEADLINE> China Beats Hong Kong to Reach Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China blanked Hong
Kong 3-0 to move into the women's team semi-finals at the World
Table Tennis Championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
World No. 1 Deng Yaping beat Wong Ching in straight sets and Li
Ju put China 2-0 ahead by beating Cha Po Wa in the second
rubber.
</P>
<P>
Yang Ying, ranked fourth in the world, completed the winning
tally with a straight set victory over Song Ah Sim.
</P>
<P>
China is the defending champion in the last world championships
with Hong Kong in the third place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
