<HEADLINE> UNHCR Urged to Repatriate Refugees in 60 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Zaire's rebel leader Laurent-Desire
Kabila today asked the United Nations High Commission for Refugees
(UNHCR) to repatriate within 60 days tens of thousands of Rwandan
refugees dying of hunger and disease in the region of Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he proposed to Zairian President Mobutu Sese Seko
that they meet in the Zambian capital Lusaka, according to Agence
France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted the UNHCR regional coordinator for central Africa,
Filippo Grandi, as saying that although the "ultimatum" given by
Kabila is short, the UNHCR will try to repatriate the refugees.
</P>
<P>
Kabila today also denied any involvement by his troops in the
reported massacre of the refugees near Kisangani, when he met with
U.N. humanitarian agencies officials and the European Union
special envoy to the Great Lakes region, Aldo Ajello.
</P>
<P>
Some 8,500 Hutu refugees are reportedly missing from a refugee
camp south of Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
International humanitarian groups said the rebels drove these
refugees to the nearby forests and refused to let the UNHCR
officials to repatriate them on April 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
